  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2011-11-04",
    "date": "2011-12-13T17:42:24Z",
    "text": "Encourages any new government convened in Egypt to fully allow for the freedom of religion.\n\nExpresses the belief that Egyptian law should provide for such freedom, including freedom of conversion and freedom to build houses of worship.\n\nRecommends the release of Coptic Christian prisoners from the spring 2011 protests, unless all due legal processes are timely followed.\n\nUrges the issuance of permanent licenses to monasteries, churches, synagogues, and other places of worship to build boundary fences for their safety and protection."
  },
